import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='values', bins=20, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['values'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['values'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values in the Volcano Dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='width', y='height', hue='values', palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between width and height of volcanic eruptions?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Values', loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.dates as mdates

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year

    yearly_eruptions = data.groupby('year').size().reset_index(name='eruptions')
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.lineplot(data=yearly_eruptions, x='year', y='eruptions', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of volcanic eruptions over time?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Eruptions')
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(mdates.YearLocator())
    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%Y'))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Eruptions', loc='upper left')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['values_count'] = data['values'].value_counts()
    ax = sns.barplot(x=data['values'], y=data['values_count'], data=data, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the most common value associated with volcanic eruptions?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Values')
    plt.ylabel('Counts')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Values', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
